name: Ab Wheel
description:
1. Hold the ab wheel with both hands and kneel on the floor. 
2. Place the ab roller on the floor in front of your knees. This is your starting position.

name: Plank
description: 1. Support the body by the forearms and the toes on the floor while bracing the core.

name: Bicep Curl (Barbell)
description: 1. Stand while holding the barbell at shoulder width with an underhand grip and elbows touching the side of the torso.

name: Bench Dip
description: 1. NOTE: To increase the difficulty for this exercise, have an exercise partner place a weight plate on your lap.

name: Lat Pulldown (Cable)
description: 1. Sit on the pull down machine with knee pads adjusted to provide support, preventing your body from being pulled out of position.

name: Bent Over One Arm Row (Dumbbell)
description: 1. Kneel over side of bench by placing knee and hand of supporting arm on bench.

name: Incline Bench Press (Dumbbell)
description: 1. Lie on the incline bench holding the dumbbells with a shoulder width pronated grip.

name: Chest Dip (Assisted)
description: 1. Holding body from arms extended above the chest dip bars with knees placed on the assistance pad. This is your starting position.

name: Hip Thrust (Bodyweight)
description: 1. Lie down on the floor or a mat with your hands to the side or over the top of your head, whichever feels more stable.

name: Standing Calf Raise (Barbell)
description: 1. Place the barbell on your shoulder.

name: Lateral Raise (Dumbbell)
description: 1. Start with the dumbbells resting on the side of the thigh. The arm should be slightly bent.

name: Strict Military Press (Barbell)
description: 1. Start with barbell at slightly below chest level.

name: Stretching
description: 1. Get into stretch position and hold while breathing deeply.

name: Clean (Barbell)
description: 1. As this is a complex movement, we recommend consulting a trainer who is able to instruct you with the appropriate form and cues.

name: Jumping Jack
description: 1. Starting with feet close together and arms at the side, slightly bend the knees.

name: Muscle Up
description: 1. NOTE: You can perform this exercise on a pull up bar or rings. As this is complex movement, we recommend consulting a trainer who is able to instruct you with the appropriate form and cues.
